                "(psk)=\n",
                "# Phase-shift keying"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 1,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
                "import numpy as np\n",
                "\n",
                "import sdr\n",
                "\n",
                "%config InlineBackend.print_figure_kwargs = {\"facecolor\" : \"w\"}\n",
                "%matplotlib inline\n",
                "# %matplotlib widget\n",
                "\n",
                "sdr.plot.use_style()"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "In the {obj}`sdr` library, phase-shift keying modulation is available in the {obj}`sdr.PSK` class."
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 2,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "def analyze_psk(psk, esn0):\n",
                "    # Generate random decimal symbols\n",
                "    s = np.random.randint(0, psk.order, 100_000)\n",
                "\n",
                "    # Modulate decimal symbols to complex symbols\n",
                "    x = psk.map_symbols(s)\n",
                "\n",
                "    # Add AWGN to complex symbols to achieve desired Es/N0\n",
                "    snr = sdr.esn0_to_snr(esn0, sps=1)\n",
                "    x_hat = sdr.awgn(x, snr)\n",
                "\n",
                "    plt.figure()\n",
                "    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)\n",
                "    sdr.plot.symbol_map(psk.symbol_map, limits=(-2, 2))\n",
                "    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)\n",
                "    sdr.plot.constellation(x_hat, persistence=True, bins=150, limits=(-2, 2))\n",
                "    plt.title(f\"Constellation at {esn0} dB $E_s/N_0$\")\n",
                "    plt.suptitle(f\"{psk.order}-PSK constellation\")\n",
                "    plt.show()\n",
                "\n",
                "    y = psk.modulate(s)\n",
                "    # h_srrc = sdr.root_raised_cosine(0.1, 6, sps)\n",
                "    # tx_mf = sdr.Interpolator(sps, h_srrc)\n",
                "    # y = tx_mf(x)\n",
                "\n",
                "    plt.figure()\n",
                "    sdr.plot.time_domain(y[0:1000])\n",
                "    plt.show()"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## Constellations"
            ]
        },

        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## Error rate curves"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 7,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "def error_rates(psk, ebn0):\n",
                "    esn0 = sdr.ebn0_to_esn0(ebn0, psk.bps)\n",
                "    snr = sdr.esn0_to_snr(esn0)\n",
                "\n",
                "    ber = sdr.ErrorRate()\n",
                "    ser = sdr.ErrorRate()\n",
                "\n",
                "    for i in range(snr.size):\n",
                "        s = np.random.randint(0, psk.order, int(1e6))\n",
                "        a = psk.map_symbols(s)\n",
                "        a_tilde = sdr.awgn(a, snr[i])\n",
                "        s_hat, a_hat = psk.decide_symbols(a_tilde)\n",
                "\n",
                "        ber.add(ebn0[i], sdr.unpack(s, psk.bps), sdr.unpack(s_hat, psk.bps))\n",
                "        ser.add(esn0[i], s, s_hat)\n",
                "\n",
                "    return ber, ser"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 8,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "ebn0 = np.linspace(-2, 10, 20)\n",
                "\n",
                "bpsk_ber, bpsk_ser = error_rates(bpsk, ebn0)\n",
                "qpsk_ber, qpsk_ser = error_rates(qpsk, ebn0)\n",
                "psk8_ber, psk8_ser = error_rates(psk8, ebn0)\n",
                "psk16_ber, psk16_ser = error_rates(psk16, ebn0)"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "### Bit error rate curves"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 9,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "image/png": "",
                        "text/plain": [
                            "<Figure size 800x400 with 1 Axes>"
                        ]
                    },
                    "metadata": {},
                    "output_type": "display_data"
                }
            ],
            "source": [
                "plt.figure()\n",
                "ebn0 = np.linspace(-2, 10, 200)\n",
                "sdr.plot.ber(ebn0, bpsk.ber(ebn0), label=\"BPSK theoretical\")\n",
                "sdr.plot.ber(ebn0, qpsk.ber(ebn0), label=\"QPSK theoretical\")\n",
                "sdr.plot.ber(ebn0, psk8.ber(ebn0), label=\"8-PSK theoretical\")\n",
                "sdr.plot.ber(ebn0, psk16.ber(ebn0), label=\"16-PSK theoretical\")\n",
                "plt.gca().set_prop_cycle(None)\n",
                "sdr.plot.ber(*bpsk_ber.error_rates(), linestyle=\"none\", marker=\".\", label=\"BPSK simulated\")\n",
                "sdr.plot.ber(*qpsk_ber.error_rates(), linestyle=\"none\", marker=\".\", label=\"QPSK simulated\")\n",
                "sdr.plot.ber(*psk8_ber.error_rates(), linestyle=\"none\", marker=\".\", label=\"8-PSK simulated\")\n",
                "sdr.plot.ber(*psk16_ber.error_rates(), linestyle=\"none\", marker=\".\", label=\"16-PSK simulated\")\n",
                "plt.ylim(1e-6, 1e0)\n",
                "plt.title(\"Bit error rate curves for PSK modulation in AWGN\")\n",
                "plt.show()"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "### Symbol error rate curves"

            "source": [
                "plt.figure()\n",
                "esn0 = np.linspace(-4, 16, 200)\n",
                "sdr.plot.ser(esn0, bpsk.ser(esn0), label=\"BPSK theoretical\")\n",
                "sdr.plot.ser(esn0, qpsk.ser(esn0), label=\"QPSK theoretical\")\n",
                "sdr.plot.ser(esn0, psk8.ser(esn0), label=\"8-PSK theoretical\")\n",
                "sdr.plot.ser(esn0, psk16.ser(esn0), label=\"16-PSK theoretical\")\n",
                "plt.gca().set_prop_cycle(None)\n",
                "sdr.plot.ser(*bpsk_ser.error_rates(), linestyle=\"none\", marker=\".\", label=\"BPSK simulated\")\n",
                "sdr.plot.ser(*qpsk_ser.error_rates(), linestyle=\"none\", marker=\".\", label=\"QPSK simulated\")\n",
                "sdr.plot.ser(*psk8_ser.error_rates(), linestyle=\"none\", marker=\".\", label=\"8-PSK simulated\")\n",
                "sdr.plot.ser(*psk16_ser.error_rates(), linestyle=\"none\", marker=\".\", label=\"16-PSK simulated\")\n",
                "plt.ylim(1e-6, 1e0)\n",
                "plt.title(\"Symbol error rate curves for PSK modulation in AWGN\")\n",
                "plt.show()"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "## Symbol mapping"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "The mapping of decimal symbols to complex symbols is important.\n",
                "Ideally, adjacent symbol errors only result in 1 bit error.\n",
                "This is generally accomplished using a Gray code (the default in :class:`sdr.PSK`)."
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 11,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "psk8_bin = sdr.PSK(8, symbol_labels=\"bin\")\n",
                "psk8_gray = sdr.PSK(8, symbol_labels=\"gray\")"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 12,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "image/png": "",
                        "text/plain": [
                            "<Figure size 800x400 with 2 Axes>"
                        ]
                    },
                    "metadata": {},
                    "output_type": "display_data"
                }
            ],
            "source": [
                "plt.figure()\n",
                "plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)\n",
                "sdr.plot.symbol_map(psk8_bin.symbol_map, limits=(-2, 2))\n",
                "plt.title(f\"Symbol map for binary coded 8-PSK\")\n",
                "plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)\n",
                "sdr.plot.symbol_map(psk8_gray.symbol_map, limits=(-2, 2))\n",
                "plt.title(f\"Symbol map for gray coded 8-PSK\")\n",
                "plt.show()"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "Since adjacent symbol errors can lead to multiple bit errors, binary-coded 8-PSK has worse bit error performance."
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": 13,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [
                {
                    "data": {
                        "image/png": "",
                        "text/plain": [
                            "<Figure size 800x400 with 1 Axes>"
                        ]
                    },
                    "metadata": {},
                    "output_type": "display_data"
                }
            ],
            "source": [
                "plt.figure()\n",
                "ebn0 = np.linspace(-2, 10, 200)\n",
                "sdr.plot.ber(ebn0, sdr.PSK(8, symbol_labels=\"bin\").ber(ebn0), label=\"8-PSK w/ binary code\")\n",
                "sdr.plot.ber(ebn0, sdr.PSK(8, symbol_labels=\"gray\").ber(ebn0), label=\"8-PSK w/ gray code\")\n",
                "plt.title(\"Bit error rate curves for 8-PSK modulation in AWGN\")\n",
                "plt.show()"
            ]
